    "about": {
      "description": "Squashfs is a highly compressed read-only filesystem for Linux.\nIt uses either gzip/xz/lzo/lz4 compression to compress both files, inodes\nand directories.  Inodes in the system are very small and all blocks are\npacked to minimise data overhead. Block sizes greater than 4K are supported\nup to a maximum of 1Mbytes (default block size 128K).",
      "home": "https://sourceforge.net/projects/squashfs/",
      "license": "GPL-2.0-or-later",
      "license_family": "GPL-2.0-or-later",
      "license_file": "COPYING",
